The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Indo-Pak ODI in July

London: India and Pakistan are likely to play a one-dayer in Glasgow in the first week of July. 

A leading Asian broadcaster, which has earlier arranged India-Pakistan match in Canada, has been surveying locations for the encounter, according to a Scottish daily. 

The proposed India-Pakistan encounter is being promoted by one of Asias leading broadcast networks, who have staged similar events in Canada, said the report. 

It is believed that the game will take place on July 4, two days after Scotland square up to Pakistan. 

